news_insight_text_link.news_insight_description: Caeli Wind, established in 2022 by its founders, has successfully raised €11M in a Series A funding round to enhance its digital platform for wind energy site analysis and marketing. This Berlin-based company's funding aims to expand its innovative platform, further developing its capabilities in the wind energy sector.

overview_description.description: Caeli Wind is a digital marketplace that identifies wind potential locations for landowners and enables professional AI-supported analysis and marketing. Their mission is to accelerate the expansion of wind turbines and increase the likelihood and speed of realisation in the wind industry. Their software checks all the criteria, from regional planning and grid connection to economic efficiency.

about_short_description.short_description: Digital marketplace that identifies wind potential locations for landowners and enables professional AI-supported analysis and marketing.

product.name: Caeli Grundstücks-Check (Caeli Property Check)
product.description: A free and anonymous online tool that allows landowners to assess the suitability of their property for wind energy by marking their land on the platform.

product.name: Windkraft-Eignungsanalyse (Wind Energy Suitability Analysis)
product.description: A service that analyzes the wind energy potential and fair achievable lease of a property using advanced software during an initial consultation.

product.name: Bundesweite Ausschreibungen (Nationwide Tenders)
product.description: A service that helps landowners find the best partner for wind energy projects through nationwide tenders.
